A mother and son on Monday were mauled to death by two dogs who broke out of their kennel in Simur sublocation in Ugenya subcounty. Caren Akinyi Aluoch, 28, and her one-year-old son were killed by the two black dogs in Siranga Trading Centre. The dogs  beaten to death by villagers. They were said to belong to Felix Omach, a Catholic priest whose whereabouts were not immediately known. He is said to have gone to the DRC where he used to work. Police were looking for him. The killer dogs were starving following their owner's absence. They broke out on Sunday night. The woman was in the habit of rising very early and walking about the the streets, a resident said. Ugenya deputy OCPD James Ngao confirmed the incident. “The home manager reported that the dogs had broken out of the homestead. The woman and her child were found Monday morning having been mauled by the cruel dogs,” Ngao said. The bodies of the woman and her son were taken to Ukwala Subcounty Hospital Mortuary. (Edited by V. Graham)